<article role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="url-shortener">
<div class="page-header">
  <h1><strong>Url Shortener</strong></h1>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-12 col-xs-12">
    <h2 class="text-primary">API usage</h2>
    <h3><strong>Request</strong></h3>
    <p><code>https://api-b.herokuapp.com/api/shorten?<strong>query string</strong></code></p>
    <p>Where <code><strong>query string</strong></code> is in this format: <code><strong>url=[url to shorten]</strong></code></p>
    <p>The Url you want to shorten must contain the protocol.</p>
    <p>Exemple:</p>
    <p><code><strong>https://api-b.herokuapp.com/api/shorten?url=https://google.com</strong></code></p>
    <h3><strong>Response</strong></h3>
    <p>If the query contains a valid url, you'll get a response in this format</p>
    <pre>
    {
      "url": "https://google.com",
      "short_url": "https://api-b.herokuapp.com/rJtzcNRix"
    }
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>
</article>

